CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, page 11, reads: "Attend UNCF Meeting - Opening the 1958-58 United Negro College Fund campaign last Friday were these dignitaries. Left to right, Dr. Hollis F. Price, president of LeMoyne College, Memphis, Tenn., a member college; Mrs. Johnnie Mai Lampkin, president of the education board of Omega Grand Chapter OES, and the Rev. J. A. Williams, Baptist Temple Church, co-chairman of the Pittsburgh campaign. The Rev, Mr. Williams presided at the dinner meeting held at the Greene Hearthe. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: President of LeMoyne College Dr. Hollis F. Price, Mrs. Johnnie Mai Lampkin, and Rev. J. A. Williams, gathered for 1958-59 United Negro College fund campaign at Greene Hearth
